SIMPLE: heartleaf
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: heartleaf
<hw>heartleaf</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>wild
ginger (<spn>Asarum shuttleworthii</spn>) having persistent heart-shaped
pungent leaves, growing from Western Virginia to Alabama.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Asarum shuttleworthii</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An evergreen low-growing perennial
(<spn>Asarum virginicum</spn>) having mottled green and silvery-gray
heart-shaped pungent leaves, growing from Virginia to South
Carolina.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Asarum virginicum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heartless</ent>⟦br⟧
